-- Toll Chief Executive Little Expected to Retire Next Year, Australian Says
-- B y   N i c h o l a   S a m i n a t h e r
-- 2010-10-26T20:29:47Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-26/toll-chief-executive-little-expected-to-retire-next-year-australian-says.html
Toll Holdings Ltd. Chief Executive
Officer Paul Little is expected to retire next year, the
Australian newspaper reported, without citing anyone. Chairman
Ray Horsburgh is expected to announce Little’s retirement at the
company’s annual general meeting on Oct. 29, the newspaper said.
Little, who helped create Toll 24 years ago, plans to return to
the board after a year or two, according to the report.  To contact the reporter on this story:
